---
layout: 'layouts/home.njk'
---

{% set maxPosts = 3 %}

{% macro postList(items) %}
<ul class="post-list">
{% for item in items %}
  <li class="post-list-item">
    {{ item.data.title }}
  </li>
{% endfor %}
</ul>
{% endmacro %}

<div class="content">
    <section>
        <p>Hello! I'm <strong>Sean</strong>, a design technologist and software engineering leader who is interested in creative tools, tools for thought, malleable systems, the open web, human-computer interaction, sustainable computing, and generally anything related to making computers more inclusive, empowering, and convivial.</p>
        <p>This site is my blog and "<a href="https://maggieappleton.com/garden-history">digital garden</a>," a collection of <a href="/blog/">writing</a> and <a href="/notes/">notes</a> on topics of personal interest.
    </section>
    <hr>
    <section>
        <h2>Latest blog posts</h2>
        {{ postList(collections.blog.slice(-1 * maxPosts)) }}
        <a href="/blog/">More posts in the archives</a>
        {% if collections.blog.length > maxPosts %}
        <a href="/blog/">More posts in the archives</a>
        {% endif %}
    </section>
    <hr>
    <section>
        <h2>Latest in the stream</h2>
        {{ postList(collections.stream.slice(-1 * maxPosts)) }}
        {% if collections.blog.length > maxPosts %}
        <a href="/blog/">More posts in the archives</a>
        {% endif %}
    </section>
</div>
